#ROOMS
#1150
@@dThe Iron Gate of Thornwood@@N~
@@dA pair of massive wrought-iron gates stand twisted and overgrown, their ornamental thorns
indistinguishable now from the real briars that have wound through every bar. Beyond, a
cracked cobblestone path disappears into a canopy of dead oaks whose bare branches mesh
together like interlocked fingers. A cold wind bleeds through the gaps and carries with
it the smell of damp stone and old blood. Mossy runes are carved into the gateposts, too
worn to read, though something about their shapes makes the eye slide away.@@N
