#1151
@@dThe Cobblestone Approach@@N~
@@dThe path is ancient and heaved, pushed up in places by roots that have grown thick as
thighs beneath it. Thorned vines have claimed the verge on both sides, their red-black
stems beaded with dew that does not quite look like water. The great gate is visible
behind you, and ahead the path bends toward a structure whose peaked roof rises above
the tree line. Crows watch from the dead oaks in absolute silence.@@N
