#1152
@@dThe Eastern Boneyard Path@@N~
@@dThe path here has been almost entirely consumed by pale root-mass that surges up through
the cobbles and spreads in every direction. Scattered among the roots are bones, too
many and too varied to be accidental. A carved stone marker leans at a sharp angle, the
epitaph ground away to nothing. The trees here are older, their bark black and glistening
as if perpetually wet. The sound of wind through the branches has a quality that almost
resembles language.@@N
