#1153
@@dThe Western Gloaming Trail@@N~
@@dThis spur off the main approach dips into a shallow depression where fog collects at all
hours. The ground here is soft and takes footprints readily, and among the prints already
pressed into the mud are shapes that do not belong to any ordinary creature. A stand of
iron-barked trees has grown in a near-perfect ring, their canopies fused at the top to
form a lightless vault. Something pale hangs at the center of the ring, turning slowly.@@N
