#1154
@@dThe Hanging Tree Circle@@N~
@@dThe pale thing that turns at the center of the iron-barked ring is a coat of ancient
chainmail, empty, hanging from a branch by its own hood. Around the base of the central
tree, finger-thick black thorns have grown in concentric spirals, each ring crusted with
old rust that is not rust. The fog here refuses to disperse regardless of any wind, and
the temperature is noticeably lower than even the cold surroundings. A narrow game trail
leads west into deeper wilderness.@@N
