#1155
@@dThe Broken Sundial Grove@@N~
@@dA stone sundial stands in a clearing, its gnomon snapped off and replaced at some point
with what appears to be a femur, though it has since been overgrown. The sundial reads
the wrong time regardless of the light. The trees here have shed their bark entirely,
standing pale and smooth as skinned animals, their crowns bearing only a few dark leaves.
A rusted iron lantern hangs from a shepherd's hook near the path, its flame extinguished
long enough ago that the oil has congealed to amber.@@N
