#1156
@@dThe Thornwood Charnel Verge@@N~
@@dThe ground to either side of the path has been disturbed here, repeatedly and extensively.
Mounds of dark earth are heaped in irregular rows between the trees, many of them
sunken, a few of them showing signs of recent disturbance from below. The smell is
thick and sweetish. Pale blue wisps drift at ankle height among the mounds, illuminating
nothing useful but casting moving shadows on the tree trunks. A stone archway, carved
with screaming faces, marks the entrance to the courtyard ahead.@@N
