#1157
@@dThe Wild Hunt's Rest@@N~
@@dThis remote clearing shows signs of recent occupation: a firepit ringed with skulls
used as candle-holders, a rack of antlers driven into the earth to hang strips of
cured meat, and trampled ground from large hooves. The trees here have been marked at
eye level with hooked symbols in bark, painted fresh in something dark. The smell of
woodsmoke and wet fur lingers. A narrow path doubles back east, and a root-swallowed
ruin rises from the undergrowth to the south.@@N
