#1158
@@dThe Mire Verge@@N~
@@dThe trail ends abruptly at the edge of a mire that smells of sulfur and black water.
Stepping stones of mossy granite lead south into the fog, but several of them have
sunk at angles that suggest the ground beneath them is unstable. Pale reeds cluster
at the water's edge, their stems rattling though there is no wind here. Something
beneath the surface occasionally breaks the tension of the water without fully emerging.@@N
