#1159
@@dThe Bone Weaver's Hollow@@N~
@@dA natural hollow in the hillside has been expanded by digging and shored up with skulls
mortared together with grey clay. The entrance is just large enough to duck through, and
the interior smells of chalk dust and old marrow. Thousands of small bones have been
woven together on the walls using wire and gut into complex geometric patterns that
vibrate at a frequency felt more than heard. The hollow opens again to the east and south.@@N
