#1160
@@dThe Courtyard of Broken Monuments@@N~
@@dA wide courtyard paved in dark slate, cracked and heaved by decades of frost and root.
Several stone monuments line the perimeter, each one depicting a figure in agony, the
faces worn smooth by time. In the courtyard's center, a dry fountain holds a statue
of a woman with her arms raised and her stone eyes hollow. The estate's main facade
looms to the south, its windows dark and its stonework draped in ivy so old it has
calcified against the wall. Twin iron braziers flank the entrance, cold and long unlit.@@N
