#1161
@@dThe Ruined Groundskeeper's Lodge@@N~
@@dOnly three walls remain of this modest stone building, the fourth collapsed into a fan
of rubble that the forest has been slowly digesting. A rusted iron stove stands open-
mouthed in the corner, filled with bird nests. The timber of the ceiling has rotted and
fallen, lying in a lattice of grey beams across the earthen floor. Old tools hang from
the remaining walls: mattocks, bill hooks, a handsaw whose teeth have rusted into one
solid mass. The smell of damp char suggests something here burned once, badly.@@N
