#1162
@@dThe Sunken Mire Path@@N~
@@dStepping stones lead through the mire along a route marked by poles driven into the
mud and capped with lanterns whose oil has long since been exhausted. The black water
on either side moves in slow, purposeful eddies. Tufts of marsh grass cling to the
stones, and in the reeds, something that might be a nest is built up on a platform of
sticks and matted fur. The path continues south through the fog to a low island.@@N
