#1163
@@dThe Hollow Ossuary Wall@@N~
@@dThe outer wall of some forgotten ossuary, just the wall itself remaining upright.
Niches set into the stonework hold the neat stacks of skulls and long bones typical of
the form, but they also hold stranger things: a clock with no face, a glass jar of
teeth arranged by size, a doll constructed from bird bones and wire. The mortar holding
the niches shut has been broken on several, the contents removed. Fresh scratch marks
on the stone suggest something large has been here recently.@@N
