#1164
@@dThe Grave-Root Passage@@N~
@@dTree roots as thick as torsos have punched through an ancient stone wall here, widening
a gap that was once a doorway into a low tunnel of root and stone. The ceiling is
knotted root-mass, and the floor is packed earth shot through with smaller roots. Old
grave markers, displaced by root growth, lean at angles throughout the passage. The
names on them have been overwritten in a language that uses no alphabet recognizable
to any living scholar.@@N
