#1166
@@dThe Gatekeeper's Watch Post@@N~
@@dA small stone booth that once housed the gatekeeper stands just inside the estate wall.
Its window faces the approach, and the small iron shutter can still be operated, though
it opens only to the first few inches now. Inside, a high stool faces the window, its
legs carved with tallies in the hundreds. A log book remains on the sill, its pages
fused by damp, the ink run into indecipherable grey clouds. A half-burned candle stub
stands on a saucer of hardened wax. The estate wall runs east and west.@@N
