#1167
@@dThe Estate Wall Walkway - West@@N~
@@dA narrow walkway runs along the top of the estate wall, accessible by a short set of
stone steps. From here one can see the courtyard below and the wilder grounds beyond
the wall, where the thornwood encroaches against the stone in ragged waves. The
parapet is crumbling in places. A gargoyle crouches at the far west end, one of a pair;
its twin has fallen and lies broken in the courtyard below. Strange scorch marks on the
parapet stones suggest this walkway has seen violence of a peculiar kind.@@N
