#1168
@@dThe Ruined Stables@@N~
@@dThe stable's roof has partially collapsed, the fallen timbers now home to a colony
of roosting crows that fill the air with low muttering at all times. The stalls remain,
twelve of them, each one showing the marks of something large and not entirely equine:
the iron manger fittings twisted, the wooden walls deeply scored by hooves at the wrong
height, chains hammered into the back wall at a height suggesting the occupant was
upright. Two of the stalls still have their gate chains intact. The smell is old and
animal and wrong.@@N
