#1169
@@dThe Mire Isle - Fog Shrine@@N~
@@dA small island of raised peat stands at the center of the worst of the mire, accessible
only via the stepping-stone path. On it stands a shrine of uncertain vintage: a stone
platform bearing offerings of corroded bronze coins, antlers, and the careful arrangement
of every small bone from a large animal, laid out in anatomical order with none missing.
The shrine figure itself is obscured by iron rings driven into it so completely the
original form is unguessable. A cold light sometimes pulses from beneath the island.@@N
