#1170
@@dThe Sunken Crypt Antechamber@@N~
@@dA flight of stone stairs leads down from the ossuary wall into a low antechamber whose
ceiling barely clears a tall person's head. The walls are smooth and damp and have been
inscribed with text in an antique liturgical hand, too dense to read at a glance and
covering every surface including the floor. A stone font stands filled with dark water,
a ring of dead flowers floating on its surface. An iron door with no handle stands in
the south wall, open enough to pass through sideways. The air is very cold.@@N
