#1171
@@dThe Root Tomb@@N~
@@dThis chamber has been formed entirely by root-mass: great roots from above have pushed
through the earth ceiling and formed a vaulted space, encasing stones and fragments of
old masonry in their coils as they descended. Several grave-slabs have been tipped
vertical and now stand as walls within the space, their carvings of the deceased still
clearly visible though the faces have been systematically defaced. A pool of very still,
very dark water occupies the western half of the chamber.@@N
