#1173
@@dThornwood Hall - The Receiving Room@@N~
@@dThe receiving room is furnished with care that has since been undone by time: chairs
upholstered in black velvet, now shredded; a writing desk of dark wood, its surface
carved with the estate's thorn motif; curtains of deep purple, thick with dust; a
sideboard displaying silverware arranged with perfect precision, none of it tarnished
despite the apparent age of the room. A fireplace with a carved stone surround dominates
the north wall, its grate holding a fire that has not been lit in years but whose ash
is arranged in a particular pattern. The smell here is of old roses and old grief.@@N
