#1174
@@dThornwood Hall - The Servant's Passage@@N~
@@dA narrow stone passage behind the main hall, low-ceilinged and smelling of mildew.
Hooks along one wall held lanterns; several still do, their glass sooty and black.
The floor here is worn smooth in the center by foot traffic, the edges rough stone.
A dumbwaiter shaft opens in the north wall, its rope intact and its counterweight
somewhere in the dark above. The passage leads west along the back of the hall
and connects to the kitchen court to the south.@@N
