#1175
@@dThe Overgrown Herb Garden@@N~
@@dThis walled garden was once cultivated, and the planting beds are still legible, though
what grows in them now grows without guidance. Herbs of a deep, almost black green crowd
every surface, and their smell is simultaneously medicinal and corrupt. A stone trough
for washing roots stands filled with opaque rainwater. An iron sundial identical to the
one in the grove outside the estate stands here, also with a bone gnomon. Someone
tended this garden recently: several beds have been freshly turned, and cuttings left
in neat bundles.@@N
