@@dThe Estate Wall - East Postern@@N~
@@dA small postern gate set into the east wall of the estate, low and arched and faced
with stone carved into a continuous vine-and-thorn motif that mirrors the hall's
interior details. The gate is iron and currently closed, though its lock mechanism
has been defeated at some point and the door merely rests shut. Beyond the wall,
the eastern grounds slope toward the mire. A path leads south along the inside of
the wall toward the kitchen court.@@N
