#1178
@@dThe Inner Crypt@@N~
@@dThe inner crypt runs east-west beneath the ossuary wall, its ceiling low and vaulted
and its walls lined with stone sarcophagi. Most of the lids have been displaced,
some pushed off from inside. The contents of the displaced tombs, where present,
have been rearranged: bones sorted by type and stacked with inhuman neatness. The
smell of old stone is threaded with something alive and wrong. The writing on the
walls here is older and cruder than the antechamber above, done with a sharp implement
directly into the stone rather than inscribed with a chisel.@@N
