#1179
@@dBelow the Root Tomb@@N~
@@dA narrow shaft in the root-mass floor of the tomb above widens as it descends into a
natural cave whose walls are slick with mineral seepage. The light from above does not
reach here. The cave runs east and north, and its walls are marked with handprints in
pigment so old the ochre has dried to a colour like dried blood. A deposit of pale
crystal juts from one wall in a column the height of a man, and it emits the faintest
cold glow.@@N
