#1180
@@dThornwood Hall - The Map Room@@N~
@@dShelf upon shelf of rolled maps, charts, and folded documents line every wall, many of
them water-damaged and fused to their neighbors. The single clear wall holds a very large
map of the Thornwood estate and its surrounding area, drawn in obsessive detail. This map
shows features that are not on any other map and includes annotations in a cramped hand
that becomes increasingly difficult to read toward the edges of the map, as if the author
was writing faster and smaller as things got worse. A large wooden table dominates the
room's center, its surface stained with the overlapping rings of hundreds of cups.@@N
