#1181
@@dThornwood Hall - The Lower Guest Wing@@N~
@@dFour doors open off this corridor, one on each side and one at each end. The doors
closest to the portrait gallery are sealed from outside with iron bars recently added.
The other doors stand open. Fragments of personal effects are scattered throughout the
corridor, as if the former occupants of the sealed rooms left in a hurry: a broken
boot, a torn coat, a single glove. The wallpaper here is the same thorn pattern as the
gallery, but some of the thorns are wet.@@N
