#1182
@@dThornwood Hall - The Dining Room@@N~
@@dA long dining table runs the length of the room, set for a meal that was never finished:
plates still bearing petrified food, glasses still holding a residue the color of old
wine. The chairs on one side have been pushed back in a single motion. The chairs on
the other side have not been disturbed at all. A massive iron chandelier above holds
thirty candles, their wax long since run down the iron into congealed cataracts. The
hearth at the room's end is large enough to stand in, and the fireplace surround is carved
with a hunting scene in which the hunters and quarry are indistinguishable.@@N
