@@dThornwood Hall - The Study Anteroom@@N~
@@dThe anteroom outside the study holds a secretary's desk bearing a neat collection of
correspondence, each letter sealed with black wax impressed with a thorn motif. None
of them have been opened. A coat rack holds three coats, and the boots beneath them
are muddy, the mud still fresh. A small clock on the wall has stopped at the same time
as the sundial outside. The door to the study proper is of heavier construction than
the surrounding walls, which says something about what is behind it.@@N
