#1186
@@dThe Physic Garden@@N~
@@dThe physic garden is more orderly than the herb garden beside it, though the plants
growing here are of a kind that no licensed apothecary would stock. The labels on the
planting markers are in the estate's cramped house hand and identify preparations that
suggest purposes: preserving, slowing, unmaking. The beds are raised and stone-edged,
and the soil within them is of an unusual dark color that does not look like ordinary
earth. A low stone building at the garden's east end holds the tools of distillation:
alembics, coils of copper tubing, a cooling tank fed by a pipe from somewhere.@@N
