@@dThe East Kitchen Garden@@N~
@@dThis garden produces food, or once did: the vegetable beds have been overtaken by
something with deep black roots that produces no fruit recognizable as food. The
climbing plants on the east-wall trellis have escaped the wall entirely and now cover
several feet of ground on the outside. A scarecrow in the garden's center has been
dressed with what appears to be genuine armor, and someone has carefully positioned
its arm to point toward the mire.@@N
