#1188
@@dThe Eastern Crypt Passage@@N~
@@dThe crypt passage extends east beneath the grounds, its ceiling low and pressed from
above by the weight of the earth over it. Vaulted brick arches, many cracked, support
the tunnel at intervals. The inscribed text on the walls continues here, and in this
stretch it has clearly been added to at different times by different hands. The oldest
text is in an ancient liturgical script; the newest is scratched in charcoal and reads
as a warning, the specific nature of which is clear only to those who understand the
old notation system it employs.@@N
