#1189
@@dThe Western Crypt Passage@@N~
@@dThe western arm of the crypt passage is shorter than the eastern, ending at a wall of
relatively new masonry that closes off what was once a further passage. The brickwork
of the closure is competent but hurried: the mortar lines are uneven, and the bricks
themselves are mismatched in color and size. Something on the other side of the wall
occasionally makes a sound. There is a small stone niche in the south wall of the passage,
and inside it, a candle stub that someone relights regularly.@@N
