#1190
@@dThe Crystal Cave Passage@@N~
@@dThe natural cave here opens into a passage whose walls are sheeted in pale mineral
deposits that catch and reflect any light source, multiplying it into something almost
bright. The deposits grow in formations suggesting the insides of geodes, and several
have been broken off, the breaks fresh and clean. The passage connects north and south
and leads deeper into the cave system to the east. Scratch marks on the floor suggest
something has been dragged through here, toward the east.@@N
