#1191
@@dThe Cave of Handprints@@N~
@@dThis chamber is entirely covered in handprints, floor to ceiling, every surface. They
overlap in palimpsest, oldest darkest, newest still slightly tacky. They are all right
hands, all the same size, spread-fingered in the same posture as the family in the hall
portrait. The ceiling at the chamber's center is too high to reach from the floor, but
the prints are there nonetheless. At the chamber's north end, a spring wells up in a
stone basin, its water cold and perfectly clear. The basin's edge is carved with the
same thorn-and-mouth motifs seen throughout the estate.@@N
