@@dThe Open Guest Room@@N~
@@dUnlike its sealed neighbors, this room appears largely undisturbed: a bed made with
military precision, a wardrobe containing clothing folded with the same precision,
a writing desk bearing a single unfinished letter. The letter is addressed to someone
whose name has been methodically removed from every mention, and concerns an upcoming
visit to the estate and the author's excitement about seeing the gardens again. The
date on the letter is several decades ago. A fresh flower in a vase on the windowsill
is the only obviously impossible thing.@@N
