@@dThe Butler's Pantry@@N~
@@dThis small room off the dining room was the butler's domain, and the contents reflect
a mind for order and inventory. A ledger of household supplies is kept with scrupulous
care up until a certain date, after which the entries become erratic and finally stop
mid-sentence. The entry that stops mid-sentence reads: the wine cellar must not be
opened because. Shelves of crystal glasses and decanted wines still intact fill the
south wall. Behind the south door, stone steps descend into the wine cellar.@@N
