of old soap and something else, sharper. A mangle at the far end, its rollers carved
from petrified wood, still turns when pushed, and the thing it moves when turning makes
a sound like breaking glass though nothing visible is fed through it. Rope lines run
the length of the ceiling, hung with items that have been washed so many times they
have lost all color. An exterior door is bolted and wedged.@@N
