#1197
@@dThe Cold Cellar@@N~
@@dThe cold cellar dug beneath the kitchen court, lined with stone shelves bearing
the estate's preserved stores. Many of the shelves hold wax-sealed crocks, jars
of pickled things, dried bundles. The temperature here is several degrees below the
cold of the crypt. The cold comes from a drain in the center of the floor from which
cold air flows steadily up. A metal grille over the drain has been secured with new
iron bolts. Around the drain, frost flowers have formed in patterns that suggest the
inscription on the crypt walls.@@N
