whose purpose was originally drainage. The channels cut in the floor to direct water
to the central drain are still functional, but they have been supplemented with more
recently cut channels forming a pattern recognizably related to the crypt inscriptions.
The drain outlet in the south wall leads to the outside, and from it comes a faint
sound that could be the mire in wind, or could be something else. The chamber connects
east through a low arch.@@N
