@@dThe eastern passage from the crystal cave leads here: a broad, low chamber whose floor
is covered in a layer of bones two or three deep, all of them small animal bones, all of
them clean and dry. The bones crunch underfoot. The walls bear no marks or decoration.
The ceiling is low enough that a tall person must stoop, and from the ceiling at
intervals hang iron chains from which nothing depends. The chamber's east end is a
crack just wide enough to squeeze through.@@N
