@@dThe Wine Cellar@@N~
@@dThe wine cellar is extensive, running the full length of the dining room above. Racks
of bottles, most still sealed, line the walls. A tasting alcove at the far end holds
a small table and two chairs, and on the table a glass of wine that has not been drunk
and has not evaporated. The wine is a deep red so dark as to be almost black in the
cellar's limited light. Several of the wine racks have been pulled aside to reveal
the rough stone of the original cellar wall beneath, and into that wall someone has
carved the same circular inscription visible in the crypt, only here the central sigil
is different.@@N
