@@dThe Deep Undercroft@@N~
@@dThe deepest section of the undercroft, below even the main crypt, accessible only via
a steep stair from the eastern undercroft above. The ceiling is bedrock, and the walls
are earth shored up with timber. The timber shoring is old and some of it is failing.
In the center of the chamber is a stone table with iron rings bolted to its sides, and
on the table and floor around it is evidence of a ritual of significant complexity and
considerable age. Whatever the ritual accomplished, the permanent cold in this room
suggests it accomplished something.@@N
