water. Ascending through a difficult chimney climb leads to a narrow natural ledge
above the general cave level, from which the whole of the limestone chamber system
can be surveyed. From here, by certain lights, the pattern of the cave walls forms
one coherent symbol that uses the entire cave system as its medium.@@N
