#1209
@@dThe High Cave Ledge@@N~
@@dThe ledge is narrow but stable, and from here the cave system below is laid out clearly.
The pattern visible from this height is unambiguous to any student of the relevant
traditions: it is a binding circle, drawn in living stone over centuries, and it is
working. The cold that permeates the cave from the crystal heart chamber is concentrated
here, and exposed skin begins to ache within minutes. There is nothing up here except
the view, the cold, and the certain knowledge that the binding is beginning to fail.@@N
