@@N
~
@@dThe mire lurker is adapted to the worst of the thornwood's wetlands in ways that suggest
generations of specialized selection, or something worse. Its skin has the texture and
color of the mire's bottom mud, and it moves through water with no more disturbance than
a thought. On land it is slower, pulling itself upright only reluctantly. Its eyes,
solid black, are positioned to watch multiple directions simultaneously. It smells of
cold water and the specific decay smell of the mire.@@N
