come to define them rather than the other way around. The antler crown they wear is
not decorative. The hounds that ring their feet are not hounds. The horn at their
hip, when it sounds, can be heard in the world that is not this one. They carry a
black lance and wear the beast-mask of the hunt's oldest tradition. Their mount, a
thing of shadow and cold fire, waits at the tree line.@@N
~
