#1172
marrow fiend~
@@da Marrow Fiend@@N~
@@da Marrow Fiend tears at the stone floor here, pulling up the bones beneath.
@@N
~
@@dThe marrow fiend is a type of construct unique to this part of the thornwood, built by
the bone weaver at the thornwood's direction for purposes that were never explained to
the weaver. It is large: wider than it is tall, with limbs in excess of the usual
number, all of them repurposed from the earth's bone-stock. Its torso is a cage of
assembled ribs from multiple large species. It is not clever but it is persistent and
it is very hard to damage in any lasting way.@@N
~
